name: Jim L
text: Holy Smokes, this place is good.  I ate at Chick Wrap a few times during visits to the Outlet Mall in Foley and was impressed with every meal.  On my first visit I had a delicious bacon cheeseburger with fries.  They took the time to melt the cheese onto the beef patty like you would at a cookout.  Awesome!  My next visit, I had chicken strips with homemade buffalo sauce.  The chicken was very good quality and not overly breaded.  The sauce was great and just one of several I was offered.  The last item I tried was the chicken salad after hearing another customer rave about it.  No kidding, it was the best I have ever had.  If you have been missing the chicken salad from the place that is closed on Sundays, this is your new go to destination.

name: Gordon's Imagination Station
text:
Trying to be as objective as possible here. Friendly employees and fast service. However the food is overpriced but it seems like they have to charge more to make up for low sales. Everything could be knocked down about 1.50$ to 2$.

They did recommend the cheese burger but its 9$ without a drink. If I'm going to spend that much on a burger I'm gonna go to a sit down restaurant.

I got the 5 piece chicken tender for my kids to split cause we just wanted something to hold us over while the wife was shopping. I expected normal size chicken tenders except we got the mini versions. Like half the size of a chik-fil-a tender. Then they offer you only 2 sauce cups and have to charge for extra. Refills are charged and so is a cup of ice.

Short story is, they overcharge and try and bleed every extra cent out of you to try and stay afloat.

text: The food was overall super salty not worth the price for the taste nor the amount of food you get. My son didn't eat it at all. Said he's tummy was hurting. Do yourself a favor a go to foosacklys instead. Disgusting.
